main event: On October 30, 1958, in Oblong, Illinois, a round, silver object with a dark center and six smaller, solid, silver discs clustered around it in a ring formation was observed. The larger object and smaller discs moved away in different directions before regrouping and disappearing. The entire sighting lasted approximately 10 minutes before the objects accelerated out of sight.
interesting points: The sighting involved a larger object and six smaller discs in a ring formation, exhibiting behavior of regrouping and then accelerating out of sight.
The investigation officers could not confirm the reported sighting by any other source, and they failed to provide a possible explanation or suggestion concerning the identity of the objects sighted.
The objects were observed continuously for approximately 10 minutes, and no photographs or images of the sighting are included in the report.
The investigation of weather conditions and possible flights in the area failed to provide a clue to the identity of the objects sighted.

The sighting was reported to the GCI Filter Center in Terre Haute, and the investigation resulted in a meager amount of information submitted, making it difficult for the center to evaluate the sighting.
sighted object: one round, silver object with a dark center and six smaller, solid, silver discs
witnesses: Mr. Oblong, Illinois alongside an unidentified individual
